03/01/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- Police announced on Thursday (December 31st) that two men have been arrested after the brutal shooting of the mayor of a small town some 700 km north of Athens, apparently in connection with an embezzlement scheme. Triantafyllos Koukoudis was found dead early on Thursday in the trunk of his own car. According to the police, he was shot eight times, including six shots in the head. The two arrested men are the local municipal treasurer and his assistant. (AP, ANA-MPA - 31/12/09)
